|WKBClans: Warfare
|WKO---------------

|YKOThe clan system allows two clans to agree to go to war with each other.
This decision is made by the leader of each clan. All wars are set
in duration, with the smallest war allowed being 3 days. Please read
the information in |YKB"help clan_cmds" |YKOfor details about starting a war.

Once a war starts, it is impossible to initiate new members into the
clan and current members of the clan aren't allowed to leave. There
are no exceptions to this rule.

During a war, clans gain points. The points are gained by killing
members of the opposing clan.

The number of points awarded per kill is largely based by the level
difference between the killer and the victim. Members who kill
enemies of greater or equal level than themselves receive more points
than members who kill enemies at lower levels. A clan is much more
likely to win a war if everyone goes after the hardest opponent they
can successfully kill, rather than going after the weakest opponent
over and over.

During a war clan members can look at ongoing war statistics via
the |YKB'cstat' |YKOcommand. After a war, a variety of details are saved
and can be accessed via the |YKB'cwar' |YKOcommand.

There is no way to stop a war early. Once a war starts, the clans
involved must deal with it. As mentioned in |YKB'help clans'|YKO, normal
PK status is ignored during a war. Non-PKers can, and will, be
killed during a clan war. Of course, Non-PKers can kill as well. During
a low-risk clanwar, you will not lose level, stats, etc. During a 
high-risk clanwar, deaths will be treated as if you were actually
PK.

Enjoy, and may the best clan win.

